Explore the data

Understand the methodology

After an unprecedented year with elections in over 100 countries, the Blavatnik Index of Public Administration provides crucial insights for officials and ministers.

A N Other, Job title, Institution

Through the Index civil service leaders can learn from peers in countries they might not usually consider.

Y T Other, Job title, Institution

Read the foreward

Executive summary

The 2024 Blavatnik Index of Public Administration covers 129 countries across its 4 domains of strategy & leadership, public policy, national delivery, and people & processes.

Using its measurement framework, the Index brings together 168 individual data points from 24 sources. Alongside the overall results of the Index, through this website you can: read articles discussing themes and countries covered in the results and interviews with those leading reform efforts, explore the data in-depth, and read the technical methodology.

Read more about the overall Index results

Strategy & leadership

Country B ranks highest for strategy & leadership with particular strengths in strategic capacity and openness & communictions, while Country D comes highest in trust & integrity.

Read more

Public policy

Country A ranks highest for public policy, while Country C comes in top for regulation.

Read more

National delivery

Country A ranks highest for national delivery with the highest scores for both system oversight and digital services.

Read more

People & processes

Country B ranks highest for domain 4 with the highest scores for diversity & inclusion, country C ranks highest for HR management and country D comes top in procurement.

Read more

Results by regional and economic groupings

The benefit of our global approach allows for rich insights by regional and economic groupings. Country X comes top in Sub-Saharan Africa, while County Y is the highest scoring low income country.

Read more

Conclusions & next steps

The results provide an important tool to help countries learn from each other, however there remain crucial gaps in the availability of data to fully understand how public administrations compare.

Read more

Making use of the results

There are many different ways you can make use of the results from the 2024 Index, read the results content, explore the data, or read articles and interviews that provide reflections on the results.

For more ideas and details on how you can make full use of the results, read our in-depth guide.

image

Through our data explorer tool you can interrogate the results for your country in-depth, review individual metrics or download the datasets for your own further analysis.
